Wilma Mankiller, the first female chief of the Cherokee Nation, has passed away. She played a crucial role in transforming the relationship between the Cherokee Nation and the Federal Government. She was also an inspiration to women in Indian Country and across America. Mankiller received the Presidential Medal of Freedom for her vision and commitment to a brighter future for all Americans. Her legacy will continue to inspire and motivate others. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama offer their condolences to Mankiller's family, especially her husband and two daughters, as well as the Cherokee Nation and all those who were touched by her good works.